
  Shroedinger wave function for Number-Theoretic functions
-----------------------------------------------------------
November 2014

See schreod.c for details.

The code in this directory solves the 1D lattice schrodinger eqn

     (1/2) L psi + V psi = E psi

for L the laplacian:
   (L psi)(i) = -psi(i-1) + 2psi(i) - psi(i+1)

and V(i) sume number theoretic function. e.g V(i) = phi(i) the toient
function.

The totient function has eigenvalues E at:

0.215167824119994002
0.774226900722062792 (odd)
1.000
1.447032293042862003
1.948106988497122263  (odd)
2.052010128157375458
2.595139525819930620  (odd)
2.850556700275637810  (odd)
3.542497175007039716  (odd)


Curious: totient function has an eigenvalue at exactly 1.0
so does sigma_n for all values of  n (including float pt)
including negative values too ...

 wow. I wonder why, its not obvious.
